In a #large bowl{}, whisk together three packets of @Crème Fraîche{1/2%cup}, half the @Cinnamon{2%teaspoon}, @Sugar{1/4%cup}, and a pinch of @Salt{pinch}. Whisk in @water{3%cups} until no lumps remain. Stir in @Rolled Oats{3%cups} and cover with #plastic wrap{}. Refrigerate overnight until oats are tender.

> This is a big-batch recipe providing 6 servings - for 12 servings double the ingredient amounts.

> TIP: Add more sugar for sweeter oatmeal.

> TIP: Divide oats between 6 #jars{} (12 jars for 12) for an easy grab-and-go breakfast!

Wash and dry produce. Peel, core, and dice @Apple{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Sliced Almonds{1/2%ounce}, @Shredded Coconut{1/4%cup}, @Brown Sugar{2%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @Salt{pinch}; toast until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pot.

Melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} in same pot over medium heat. Add apple and remaining cinnamon; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @Brown Sugar{1%tablespoon}, @water{1/2%cup}, @Sugar{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @Salt{pinch}; stir to combine. Cook, covered, until apple is tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Uncover pot and increase heat to medium-high. Cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid is thickened and syrupy, ~{3-5%minutes} more. Transfer to a second small bowl.

While apple cooks, in a third small bowl, mix @Peach Jam{1} and remaining crème fraîche until smooth.

Tightly cover apple compote and peach cream with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve. Store coconut almond crunch in an #airtight container{}.

When ready to eat, divide overnight oats between #bowls{}. Top with @Dried Apricots{2%ounce}, apple compote, coconut crunch, and peach cream as desired.

> TIP: Microwave compote for ~{30%seconds} if you like!